spanGrp.span: Me, I will tell my story here with Richard
anin gidabalol hadis aa gandaw Richard
ànín gìdàbàlól hàdís àà gàndàw Rìchárd
mimi nitazungumza hadithi yangu nikiwa na Richard
In the old days my father told me "I was born in Dongobesh"
zamani baba yangu aliniambia kuwa yeye alizaliwa Dongobeshi
"I was born in Dongobesh and I lived there when I grew up"
gejilsinan dung'obesh aa gabidew dung'obesh am ahedu
'géjílsínàn dùng''òbésh àà gàbìdéw dùng''òbésh àm àhédú'
nilizaliwa Dongobesh na niliishi uko nilipokua
"We were forced to move to go..."
"We went to Mbulu and we lived there"
"We went to Qurus and live there"
"We were already started to become adults and then we came to Mang'ola"
'tulikuwa tumeshaanza kuwa watu wazima tukaja Mang''ola'
"We came to Mang'ola and when we arrived"
"We farmed the earth and the crops grew, well, then I married"
geabarj darord am iheas agwayd bas geafkaby qawuny ha agageshi
géabàrj dàròrd àm ìhéas àgwàyd bàs géafkàby qàwúny hà àgàgéshì
tukalima ardhi na mazao yalipoiva basi nikaja nikaoa
qamn gamad mi ni gil qodes quwar
qàmn gàmàd mí ní gìl qòdés qùwàr
mama yako sasa ndiyo huyo amekuwa na familia
"She already became my wife, the daughter of Jabanja"
qowu ajnochandeny ni garmodenyu hudab Jabanja
qòwù àjnòchàndény nì gàrmòdényú húdàb Jàbànjá
ameshakuwa mama yangu ni mke wangu binti waJabanjo
My mother in the old days
He said that when I grew up
Mangi came and asked to marry
Finally he was permitted to take me
We left and when we arrive we built our home
geang'ech ewayen ha aamisihit geadesch qahany
We build our home and we were together and later I gave birth to you all
gesiny qahany aa gendaydosch aa much dajileg ahay
gésíny qàhàny àà géndàydòsch àà múch däjílég àhày
tukajenga nyumba yetu tukawa pamoja na baadaye nikawazaa ninyi
Until I reached this time time where I am
aa dahid qat ni qamn andin
àà dàhìd qàt ní qàmn àndín
Now I don't think that I'm with a lot of people...
qamn aa mda badod gasiny buneed ga
qàmn àà mdà bàdòd gàsìny bùnééd gà
sasa huoni kuwa nimeshakuwa na watu wengi wa....
That is, I've already give birth to you all and you all should go and build your houses like Mangi and I built ours
yaani gajilew abisin ar agog awayen asin galgagw asindayd galgagw gisisindayd anin aa mangi
yààní gàjíléw àbísín àr àgóg àwàyén àsìn gàlgàgw àsíndàyd gàlgàgw gísìsìndàyd ànín àà màngí
yaani nimeshawazaa na nyinyi pia mwende mkajenge nyumba zenu kama tulivyoijenga mimi ba Mangi
stay with people and you all too
mkawe na watu na nyinyi pia
Mother and father, what they told us is this
aha gid rung'nes qamatany nihi aa baba
'àhà gìd rúng''nés qàmàtány níhì àà bàbà'
Mama na Baba walichotuambia ndiyo hicho
In the old days they came from far away, they came from Dongobesh and came to farm in Mang'ola and they married each other
qay buneed gwalab ed shag diya gwalab dung'obesh aa qafk gwarondosches mang'ol aa qafk gagenaj giyet
'qày bùnééd gwàlàb éd shàg díyà gwàlàb dúng''òbésh àà qàfk gwàròndòschés màng''òl àà qàfk gàgénàj gìyét'
'zamani watu walitoka mbali walitoka Dongobeshi wakaja kukutanikia mang''ola na wakaoana'
Until they gave birth to us
Now we're in the world, we were born by theym
qamn gend duniani geajiles saw hay
qàmn génd dùnìàní geàjílés sàw hày
sasa tupo duniani tumezaliwa na wao
Often we follow each other, this is how it is
